      "message": "I will make some Macro like MEM_TRACE(\"EMUGL\"). What would be even better implementation is some C++ magic so that this line of code only runs once. The constraint is that we need to put this line of code inside the function we want to register. Thus, the tracker will be able to infer what is the instruction pointer and how big the function is. Just passing function address won\u0027t solve the problem. But it only needs to run once. Repetitive checks are unnecessary.",
